=== cmd 0: [fork --help] ===
Manage network fork mode

Fork mode lets you test deployment scripts against local forks of live networks with snapshot/revert
workflow.

Usage: treb fork [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  enter    Enter fork mode for a network
  exit     Exit fork mode for a network
  revert   Revert the last treb run on a fork
  restart  Restart a crashed fork
  status   Show status of all active forks
  history  Show command history for a fork
  diff     Show deployments added or changed during fork mode
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also respected via NO_COLOR env var)

      --non-interactive
          Skip interactive prompts (also enabled via TREB_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, CI=true, or non-TTY
          stdin/stdout)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Use "treb fork [command] --help" for more information about a command.
